Certainly! Here's a simple example of how you can create a basic commenting system using JavaScript. This example will include:

- A textarea for users to enter their comments.
- A button to submit the comment.
- A section to display the list of comments.

### Example HTML and JavaScript:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>Comment System</title>
<style>
  #comments { margin-top: 20px; }
  .comment { border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 10px 0; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Leave a Comment</h2>
<textarea id="commentInput" rows="4" cols="50" placeholder="Write your comment..."></textarea><br/>
<button onclick="addComment()">Submit Comment</button>

<div id="comments"></div>

<script>
  function addComment() {
    // Get the comment text
    const commentText = document.getElementById('commentInput').value.trim();

    // Check if the comment is not empty
    if (commentText === '') {
      alert('Please write a comment before submitting.');
      return;
    }

    // Create new comment element
    const commentDiv = document.createElement('div');
    commentDiv.className = 'comment';

    // You could include more user info here, like a username and timestamp
    commentDiv.innerText = commentText;

    // Append the new comment to the comments section
    document.getElementById('comments').appendChild(commentDiv);

    // Clear the textarea
    document.getElementById('commentInput').value = '';
  }
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How it works:
- The user writes a comment in the textarea.
- When clicking 'Submit Comment', the `addComment()` function is triggered.
- The function retrieves the input, checks if it's not empty, creates a new `<div>` for the comment, and appends it to the page.
- The input field is then cleared for the next comment.

### Enhancements:
- Store comments persistently (e.g., with localStorage or a backend database).
- Add features like username, timestamps, editing, deleting, or replying.
- Style the comment section for better appearance.

Would you like an implementation with those features or integration with a backend?
